## Hall of Fame

Over the years, we had the pleasure to welcome a lot of amazing speakers from the Zig community.

### Zigtoberfest 2025

- *Andrew Kelley & Zig Core Team*: Zig's New Async I/O Demo
- *Lukas Pietzschmann*: Lock-free data structures in Zig
- *Loris Cro*: How To Write Better Software With Zig
- *Rene Schallner*: Running your Company on the Command-Line with Zig, LaTeX, Git, and ZAP⚡!
- *Mario Schallner*: Next-Level Terminal Games and Visuals – How Zig Powers and Accelerates a Hacker’s Dream Canvas, Adding SID Sound on Top

### Zigtoberfest 2024

- *Loris Cro*: Zine: a Static Site Generator Written in Zig
- *Mattia Maldini*: Approaches to Memory Mapped I/O
- *Lukas Pietzschmann*: Exploring properties of constraint programs
- *David Sugar*: Password Databases by Example
- *Rene Schallner*: ZML
